commit.message:
textinput: pass const char* instead of char*

widgets/numentry: handle text input directly rather than emulating keys

keyboard: completely remove 16-bit unicode field, use SDL_TEXTINPUT where possible

I'm force-pushing this commit replacing some somewhat related dmoz encoding changes, but
this PR shouldn't really encapsulate that as well. It's a good first step with new charset functions to
convert to and from UTF-8 from ITF, but not much has changed aside from that.

Ideally we would prefer UTF-8 in filenames, and if that doesn't work just display the filename as is
in ITF, no matter what could come out of it. Unfortunately Windows has problems here because UTF-16,
but there should be no problem converting to and from UTF-8 and UTF-16, so our internal representation
can remain as UTF-8 and we can use Windows system APIs to convert between the two whenever we have to
talk to the system.
Update log to reflect change in previous commit
